folder: General Health and Mood/Beck's Depression Inventory (BDI)
display_name: Beck's Depression Inventory (BDI): Summary score
description:
Calculated - Total score based on a modified Beck's Depression Inventory 20-item questionnaire (all 20 items must have response). Each item is scored on a 4 point scale (from 0-3). The total score is the mean of all 20 items, multiplied by 21, with a possible range from 0 to 63. Higher score indicates more severe depressive symptoms. A cutoff score indicative of mild depressive symptoms is greater than 10 and for severe depressive symptoms is greater than 30. [Beck's, et al., 1961 (PubMed ID: 13688369)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/13688369/)

[Search for all BDI variables within this dataset](https://sleepdata.org/datasets/sandd/variables?search=bdi)

folder: General Health and Mood/Beck's Depression Inventory (BDI)
display_name: Beck's Depression Inventory (BDI): Summary score (missing items allowed)
description:
Calculated - Total score based on a modified Beck's Depression Inventory 20-item questionnaire (missing items allowed, 14 items required). Each item is scored on a 4 point scale (from 0-3). The total score is the mean of 14 items, multiplied by 21, with a possible range from 0 to 63. Higher score indicates more severe depressive symptoms. A cutoff score indicative of mild depressive symptoms is greater than 10 and for severe depressive symptoms is greater than 30. [Beck's, et al., 1961 (PubMed ID: 13688369)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/13688369/)

[Search for all BDI variables within this dataset](https://sleepdata.org/datasets/sandd/variables?search=bdi)

folder: General Health and Mood/Revised Children's Manifest Anxiety Scale (RCMAS)
display_name: Revised Children's Manifest Anxiety Scale (RCMAS): Total anxiety score
description:
Calculated - Summary score of the Revised Children's Manifest Anxiety Scale (RCMAS), a 37-item self-report questionnaire designed to obtain information from children concerning their feelings of anxiety across several dimensions. The score is the sum of items 1, 2, 3, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 13, 14, 15, 17, 18, 19, 21, 22, 23, 25, 26, 27, 29, 30, 31, 33, 34, 35, and 37 from four subscales (i.e., physiological anxiety, worry, social anxiety and defensiveness), with possible range of 0 to 28. Higher scores indicate a greater level of anxiety. T-scores greater than 60 indicate respondent has some difficulties with anxiety. [Reynolds, C.R., and Richmond, B.O. (1985). Revised Children's Manifest Anxiety Scale. RCMAS Manual. Los Angeles: Western Psychological Services](https://doi.org/10.1177/073428298700500110)

[Search for all RCMAS variables within this dataset](https://sleepdata.org/datasets/sandd/variables?search=rcmas)

display_name: Rutter Childrens Behaviour Questionnaire (RCBQ): Total score
description:
Calculated - Total score based on 24 items from Rutter Childrens Behaviour Questionnaire (RCBQ). Sum of all responses to items 1 through 24. Higher scores indicate higher levels of behavioral problems. [Rutter M., 1967 (PubMed ID: 6033260)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/6033260/)

display_name: Variable to identify order/sequence of actigraphy days for each participant.
description: 1 is first day of recorded actigraphy, then numbers are continuous for the full time frame of their participation in the study. Variable to identify sequence in the absence of date information. Can be used to sort file in order of date of data collection in lieu of having date variable in file. NOTE: final number indicates total number of days of actigraphy data for each participant.

folder: Sleep Questionnaires/Chronotype/Smith Morningness Eveningness Questionnaire
display_name: Smith Morningness-Eveningness Questionnaire (SMEQ): Summary score (all items required)
description:
Calculated - Total score based on 13-item Smith Morningness-Eveningness Questionnaire (SMEQ). Each item is scored on a 5 point scale (from 1-5), among which items 1,2,6,7,8,9,10,12,13 are reverse coded. The total score is the sum of all 13 items ranging from 13 to 55. A total score of 22 or less indicates evening type; a total score between 23 and 43 indicates intermediate type; a total score of 44 and above indicates morning type. [Smith CS et al., 1989 (PubMed ID: 2793773)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2793773/)

[Search for all Smith Morningness-Eveningness Questionnaire variables within this dataset](https://sleepdata.org/datasets/sandd/variables?search=smeq)

folder: Sleep Questionnaires/Chronotype/Smith Morningness Eveningness Questionnaire
display_name: Smith Morningness-Eveningness Questionnaire (SMEQ): Summary score (9 out of 13 items required)
description:
Calculated - Total score based on 13-item Smith Morningness-Eveningness Questionnaire (SMEQ). Each item is scored on a 5 point scale (from 1-5), among which items 1,2,6,7,8,9,10,12,13 are reverse coded. The total score is the sum of all 13 items (9 items required) ranging from 13 to 55. A total score of 22 or less indicates evening type; a total score between 23 and 43 indicates intermediate type; a total score of 44 and above indicates morning type. [Smith CS et al., 1989 (PubMed ID: 2793773)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2793773/)

[Search for all Smith Morningness-Eveningness Questionnaire variables within this dataset](https://sleepdata.org/datasets/sandd/variables?search=smeq)
